&iacute;a Bắc, Đ&agrave; Lạt gi&aacute;p với huyện Lạc Dương, về ph&iacute;a Đ&ocirc;ng v&agrave; Đ&ocirc;ng Nam gi&aacute;p với huyện Đơn Dương, về ph&iacute;a T&acirc;y v&agrave; T&acirc;y Nam gi&aacute;p với hai huyện L&acirc;m H&agrave; v&agrave; Đức Trọng.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://phuocnh/tomatocms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cbde738539_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Chợ Đ&agrave; Lạt về đ&ecirc;m<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">H&agrave;ng trăm năm trước đ&acirc;y, Đ&agrave; Lạt l&agrave; địa b&agrave;n cư tr&uacute; của người Lạch, vốn l&agrave; cư d&acirc;n của to&agrave;n bộ cao nguy&ecirc;n Lang Biang. Đ&agrave; Lạt c&oacute; diện t&iacute;ch hơn 400 km&sup2;, bao bọc bởi c&aacute;c đỉnh n&uacute;i cao v&agrave; d&atilde;y n&uacute;i li&ecirc;n tiếp:<br /> <br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Ph&iacute;a Bắc v&agrave; T&acirc;y Bắc giới hạn bởi d&atilde;y Chorơmui, Yộ Đa Myut (1.816 m), T&acirc;y Bắc dựa v&agrave;o ch&acirc;n d&atilde;y n&uacute;i Chư Yang Kae (1.921 m), thuộc quần sơn Lang Biang m&agrave; đỉnh cao nhất l&agrave; Chư Yang Sinh (1.408 m).<br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Ph&iacute;a Đ&ocirc;ng l&agrave; ch&acirc;n d&atilde;y n&uacute;i Bi Doup (2.278 m) dốc xuống cao nguy&ecirc;n Dran.<br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Ph&iacute;a Đ&ocirc;ng Nam chắn bởi d&atilde;y Cho Proline (1.629 m).<br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Ph&iacute;a Nam v&agrave; T&acirc;y Nam c&oacute; d&atilde;y n&uacute;i Voi (1.754 m) v&agrave; Y&agrave;ng Sơreng bao bọc.</p>', 'Wikipedia', '', '15:43:30', 1, 'admin');
INSERT INTO news_article_revision (revision_id, article_id, category_id, title, sub_title, slug, description, content, author, icons, created_date, created_user_id, created_user_name) VALUES (71, 17, 1, 'Nha Trang', '', 'nha-trang', '<p>Nha Trang About this sound pronunciation is a coastal city and capital of Kh&aacute;nh H&ograve;a province, on the South Central Coast of Vietnam.</p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;">It is bounded on the North by Ninh Ho&agrave; district, on the East by the South China Sea, on the South by Cam Ranh town and on the West by Di&ecirc;n Kh&aacute;nh district. The city has about 300,000 inhabitants, a number which is projected to increase to between 500,000 and 600,000 inhabitants by 2020 according to an estimation of Nha Trang Administrative Board Statistics.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://phuocnh/tomatocms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cba2d1b84a_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Nha Trang&acute;s coastline</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Nha Trang is well known for its pristine beaches and excellent scuba diving and is fast becoming a popular destination for international tourists, attracting large numbers of backpackers as well as more affluent travelers on the Southeast Asia circuit. It is already very popular with Vietnamese tourists. Nha Trang Bay is widely considered as amongst the world''s most beautiful bays. Tourists are welcome to participate in the Sea Festival, held biennially. Nha Trang was the site of the Miss Universe 2008 Pageant on July 14, 2008 and it will also host Miss Earth 2010.<br /><br />Historically, the city was known as Kauthara under the Champa. The city is still home to the famous Po Nagar Tower built by the Champa. Being a coastal city, Nha Trang is a center for marine science based at the Nha Trang Oceanography Institute. The Hon Mun marine protected area is one of four first marine protected areas in the world admitted by the IUCN.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://phuocnh/tomatocms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cba2c0dd5e_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Nha Trang''s beach</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Commercial flights to Nha Trang no longer use the city''s municipal airport, but fly to the larger Cam Ranh International Airport, a former U.S. Air Force Base (built during the Vietnam War) located approximately 35 km south of Nha Trang (see the Transport section below for additional details).<br /><br />The French-Swiss bacteriologist Alexandre Yersin (who discovered the Yersinia pestis bacterium) identified himself with Nha Trang''s life for 50 years (affectionately known as &Ocirc;ng Năm). He established the Indochina Pasteur Institute (now known as the Nha Trang Pasteur Institute) devoted to research on the bubonic plague. Yersin died in Nha Trang on March 1, 1943. A street in the city is named after him, there is a shrine located next to his tomb, and his house has been converted into the Yersin Museum.</p>', 'Wikipedia', '', '15:43:45', 1, 'admin');
INSERT INTO news_article_revision (revision_id, article_id, category_id, title, sub_title, slug, description, content, author, icons, created_date, created_user_id, created_user_name) VALUES (72, 17, 1, 'Nha Trang', '', 'nha-trang', '<p>Nha Trang About this sound pronunciation is a coastal city and capital of Kh&aacute;nh H&ograve;a province, on the South Central Coast of Vietnam.</p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;">It is bounded on the North by Ninh Ho&agrave; district, on the East by the South China Sea, on the South by Cam Ranh town and on the West by Di&ecirc;n Kh&aacute;nh district. The city has about 300,000 inhabitants, a number which is projected to increase to between 500,000 and 600,000 inhabitants by 2020 according to an estimation of Nha Trang Administrative Board Statistics.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://phuocnh/tomatocms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cba2d1b84a_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Nha Trang&acute;s coastline</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Nha Trang is well known for its pristine beaches and excellent scuba diving and is fast becoming a popular destination for international tourists, attracting large numbers of backpackers as well as more affluent travelers on the Southeast Asia circuit. It is already very popular with Vietnamese tourists. Nha Trang Bay is widely considered as amongst the world''s most beautiful bays. Tourists are welcome to participate in the Sea Festival, held biennially. Nha Trang was the site of the Miss Universe 2008 Pageant on July 14, 2008 and it will also host Miss Earth 2010.<br /><br />Historically, the city was known as Kauthara under the Champa. The city is still home to the famous Po Nagar Tower built by the Champa. Being a coastal city, Nha Trang is a center for marine science based at the Nha Trang Oceanography Institute. The Hon Mun marine protected area is one of four first marine protected areas in the world admitted by the IUCN.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://phuocnh/tomatocms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cba2c0dd5e_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Nha Trang''s beach</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Commercial flights to Nha Trang no longer use the city''s municipal airport, but fly to the larger Cam Ranh International Airport, a former U.S. Air Force Base (built during the Vietnam War) located approximately 35 km south of Nha Trang (see the Transport section below for additional details).<br /><br />The French-Swiss bacteriologist Alexandre Yersin (who discovered the Yersinia pestis bacterium) identified himself with Nha Trang''s life for 50 years (affectionately known as &Ocirc;ng Năm). He established the Indochina Pasteur Institute (now known as the Nha Trang Pasteur Institute) devoted to research on the bubonic plague. Yersin died in Nha Trang on March 1, 1943. A street in the city is named after him, there is a shrine located next to his tomb, and his house has been converted into the Yersin Museum.</p>', 'Wikipedia', '', '15:43:45', 1, 'admin');
INSERT INTO news_article_revision (revision_id, article_id, category_id, title, sub_title, slug, description, content, author, icons, created_date, created_user_id, created_user_name) VALUES (73, 19, 13, 'Nha Trang', '', 'nha-trang', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Nha Trang l&agrave; một th&agrave;nh phố ven biển v&agrave; l&agrave; trung t&acirc;m ch&iacute;nh trị, kinh tế, văn h&oacute;a, khoa học kỹ thuật v&agrave; du lịch của tỉnh Kh&aacute;nh H&ograve;a, Việt Nam.</p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Trước khi trở th&agrave;nh phần đất của Việt Nam, Nha Trang thuộc về Chi&ecirc;m Th&agrave;nh. C&aacute;c di t&iacute;ch của người Chăm vẫn c&ograve;n tại nhiều nơi ở Nha Trang. Nha Trang được Thủ tướng ch&iacute;nh phủ Việt Nam c&ocirc;ng nhận l&agrave; đ&ocirc; thị loại 1 v&agrave;o ng&agrave;y 22 th&aacute;ng 4 năm 2009. Đ&acirc;y l&agrave; một trong 6 đ&ocirc; thị loại 1 trực thuộc tỉnh của Việt Nam<br /><br />C&aacute;c b&atilde;i biển đẹp của th&agrave;nh phố n&agrave;y đ&atilde; biến n&oacute; th&agrave;nh một danh lam thắng cảnh. Nơi đ&acirc;y cũng được biết đến như một địa điểm l&yacute; tưởng để tổ chức c&aacute;c sự kiện lớn như Festival Biển (Nha Trang), hay c&aacute;c cuộc thi sắc đẹp lớn như Hoa hậu Việt Nam, Hoa hậu Thế giới người Việt 2007 , Hoa hậu Ho&agrave;n vũ 2008, Hoa hậu Tr&aacute;i đất 2010, Hoa hậu Thế giới 2010...</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://phuocnh/tomatocms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cba2d1b84a_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><small>B&atilde;i biển Nha Trang</small></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Th&agrave;nh phố Nha Trang hiện nay c&oacute; diện t&iacute;ch tự nhi&ecirc;n l&agrave; 251 km&sup2;, d&acirc;n số 361.454 (2009). Ph&iacute;a Bắc gi&aacute;p huyện Ninh H&ograve;a, ph&iacute;a Nam gi&aacute;p huyện Cam L&acirc;m, ph&iacute;a T&acirc;y gi&aacute;p huyện Di&ecirc;n Kh&aacute;nh, ph&iacute;a Đ&ocirc;ng gi&aacute;p Biển Đ&ocirc;ng.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://phuocnh/tomatocms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7cba2c0dd5e_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Đường ven biển</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em><br /></em></p>\r\n<h2>Đồng bằng Di&ecirc;n Kh&aacute;nh - Nha Trang</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><br />Nha Trang nằm ở ph&iacute;a Đ&ocirc;ng Đồng bằng Di&ecirc;n Kh&aacute;nh - Nha Trang. Một đồng bằng được bồi lấp bởi s&ocirc;ng C&aacute;i Nha Trang c&oacute; diện t&iacute;ch gần 300 km&sup2;, địa h&igrave;nh đ&ograve;ng bằng bị ph&acirc;n h&oacute;a mạnh:<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * phần ph&iacute;a T&acirc;y dọc s&ocirc;ng Ch&ograve; từ Kh&aacute;nh B&igrave;nh đến Di&ecirc;n Đồng bị b&oacute;c m&ograve;n, độ cao tuyệt đối khoảng 10-20 m<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * phần ph&iacute;a Đ&ocirc;ng l&agrave; địa h&igrave;nh t&iacute;ch tụ độ cao tuyệt đối dưới 10m, bề mặt địa h&igrave;nh bị ph&acirc;n cắt mạnh bởi c&aacute;c d&ograve;ng chảy.</p>', 'Wikipedia', '', '15:44:04', 1, 'admin');
